****FILE COMMAND****

touch filename : used to create a file
ll : list of files (long list),it's comes from the alphbatical order ex: -rw-r--r--, 1 root root 0 JUL 17 13:53 devops (-rw-r--r-- =permitions, 1 root root = owners, 0 jul 13:53 = time, devops = file name)
ls : shoet list ex: devops ( filename)
touch filename1 filename2 filename3 : used to multiple cammands ex: touch linux jenkins git
touch filename {n..n+1} : this file create based on the give numbers we need to give muststood the two dots in between requested numbers ex: touch git {1..3} op/ git1 git2 git3
rm filename : remove file with permission ex: rm filename1 filename2 op/ rm:remove regular empty file 'filename1'? Y(we need to give 'y')
rm -f filename : remove file without permission
rm -f filename1 filename2 : remove multiple files without permission
rm -f filename{n..n+1} : this command will remove files from n to n+1 without permission
rm -f* : used to delete all files 
rm -f *.txt : used to delete all files with .txt extension
rm -f a* : This command will delete all files which are started with "A" letter

 ****FOLDER COMMANDS****

mkdir foldername : used to create a folder eex: mkdir git op/drwxr-xr-x, 2 root root 6 jul 17 14:05 git
mkdir foldername1 foldername2 : used to create a multiple folders at a time 
mkdir foldername {n..n+1} : used to create a n+1 folders at a time.
rmdir foldername : used to remove empty folder
rmdir foldername1 foldername2 : used to remove multiple empty folder
rmdir foldername{n..n+1} : used to remove a n+1 folders at a time
rmdir * : used to remove all empty folder
rmdir -rf * : used to remove all files & folder and also it is used to remove Non-empty foldes















